fieldDescription.sunRiseDescription: the moment when the upper edge of the Sun becomes visible above the horizon is called the Sunrise or the Dawn.
fieldDescription.sunSetDescription: Sunset, is the moment when the upper edge of the Sun goes below the horizon.
fieldDescription.moonRiseDescription: Moon rise refers to the time when the upper edge of the Moon becomes visible above the horizon
fieldDescription.moonSetDescription: Moonset refers to the time when the upper edge of the Moon Goes below the horizon.
fieldDescription.istkaalDescription: the time for which we seek astrological information is called "Muhurta" or the auspicious time. If a person is born at the time of Sunrise, that becomes their auspicious time. If someone is born after noon, they would need to halve the daytime
fieldDescription.localTimeCorrectionDescription: Adjustments are made to that time which can vary between the birthplace's local time and standard time used for astrological calculations.
fieldDescription.warTimeCorrectionDescription: The corrections made at that time is known as rectification, where errors due to conflicts or struggles during a person's birth time need to be corrected. This rectification is done to align astrological calculations with the correct birth time, allowing for greater accuracy in the analysis.
fieldDescription.lmtAtBirthDescription: In astrology 'Local Mean Time at Birth' (LMT at birth) refers to the use of the local time at the place of an individual's birth at the exact moment of their birth. This time is employed for calculating the positions of celestial bodies and is utilized for astrological calculations.
fieldDescription.gmtAtBirthDescription: In astrology, "GMT at Birth" refers to the time when a person was born, and at that time, Greenwich Mean Time (GMT) or Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) was in effect. This time is significant for calculating the positions of celestial bodies and assists in creating accurate astrological charts.
fieldDescription.tithiDescription: The term "Tithi" in the Hindu Panchang (calendar) indicates the day based on the moon's position in relation to the sun. It is determined by the moon's distance from the sun.
fieldDescription.hinduWeeksDaysDescription: The term "Hindu Weekdays" refers to the days of the week that are based on the names of celestial bodies according to the Hindu Panchang (calendar). These days are significant in determining auspicious days for various activities and rituals.
fieldDescription.longitudeDescription: In physical geography, "Longitude" is a celestial coordinate that indicates the distance of a location east or west. It measures the position of a location in the east-west direction and is useful in calculating the positions of celestial bodies in astrology.
fieldDescription.latitudeDescription: The term "Latitude" in geography indicates the measurement of the northward or southward position of a location and is crucial in calculating the positions of celestial bodies in astrology.
fieldDescription.payaDescription: In any kundli the placement of Moon tells about Paya and feet. In a kundli the feet are described to be of 4 types, 4 types that is - Silver, copper, Gold and Iron. The Silver feet is considered to be most auspicious. These people earn a lot of name and respect and are One with the Silver feet is considered auspicious for his/her parents too. The one with the Copper feet has good thinking. If one has a gold feet, he /she is considered inauspicious for the parents, but a kundli is also affected by many different planets also.  Iron feet are considered inausicious  These people have to lead a difficult life.
fieldDescription.varnaDescription: The meaning of Varna is nature and color. These are of 4 types - Brahmin, Khatriya, Vaishya and Shudra. Boys and girls can be of any Varna but their nature and color is determined by any one of out of these 4.
fieldDescription.vasyaDescription: Vashya means to be in control. Through astrologers, the vashya of a girl and a boy is determined by matching their charts. In astrology vashya is the significator of mental similarity of a boy and a girl. It determines the pace and understanding of a couple towards each other.
fieldDescription.yoniDescription: In this world, every living being is associated with one yoni or another. In Vedic astrology, the importance of yonis is connected to the constellations. For a successful marriage, the yoni of both the woman and the man should be the same, so that mutual understanding and compatibility can thrive. There are fourteen types of yonis, and two constellations are grouped into one yoni.
fieldDescription.ganaDescription: Humans are separated in Gana - Dev gana, Manyushya gana and Rakshas gana. Based on these the character, and nature of a person is determined
fieldDescription.nadiDescription: Nakshatra are total 27 in number and the placement of Moon in their special condition determines the Nadi. If Nadi dosha is present then a a lot of problems in a marriage can happen. The placement of the Moon in the group of 9 nakshatras form a Nadi which are has total 8 numbers. Nadi is of 3 types
fieldDescription.dasaBalanceDescription: Dasha balance is an astrological trick which is used to show the effects of the planets on the human life. In a specific time period, it represents the effective positions of various planets and assits in predicting various eventrs and circumstances in a person's life.
fieldDescription.lagnaDescription: the angle of the Eastern horizon at the time of your birth is called the Ascendant. First house in a kundli is associated to the Ascendant.
fieldDescription.lagnaLordDescription: The ruler of the first house is known as the lagna lord or the lord of the ascendant.
fieldDescription.rashiDescription: In a kundli sign in which Moon is placed is known as Rashi.
fieldDescription.rashiLordDescription: The ruler of the house in which the Moon is placed is called the Rashi lord.
fieldDescription.nakshatraPadaDescription: In Vedic astrology, a constellation is considered similar to a star. All 27 constellations are divided into 4 quarters or segments of 3 degrees 20 minutes each. Consequently, each of the nine celestial bodies in the sky has rulership over three constellations. This means that each zodiac sign contains 9 segments.
fieldDescription.nakshatraLordDescription: in a kundli , the sign in which the Moon is located is your nakshatra and the ruler of that nakshatra is called the lord of the nakshatra.
fieldDescription.julianDayDescription: Julian day is a continous count of days since the beginning of the Julian era and is primarily used by astronomers
fieldDescription.sunSignDescription: The sign in which the Sun is positioned in a kundli is referred to as th Sun sign
fieldDescription.yunjaDescription: there are 27 nakshatras, 6 form the first part, 12 form the middle part and 9 form the last part. This is known as yunja. The first 6 nakshatras - Revati, Ashwini, Bharani, Krittika, Rohini and Mrigashira. The middle part consists of 12 nakshatras - Adra, Punarvasu, Pushya, Ashlesha, Magha,
fieldDescription.tatvaDescription: According to astrology there are five elements - Earth, Water, Fire, Air and space. Water and Fire are considered adverseries, while fire and Air share a friendly relationship. There is also a reasonable rapport between air and water, However, the element space doesn't belong to any specific
fieldDescription.ghatChakrDescription: Ghaat Chakra provides information about all the inauspicious times in your life. Sometimes a day is not good for a person, because the date and constellation of that day are not auspicious. All these stages come under Ghaat Chakra.

panchangResponse.panchangDescription: The Panchang, a Hindu astrological almanac, encompasses five elements: Tithi (lunar day), Nakshatra (star constellation), Yoga, Karana, and the Hindu calendar's essential details. It guides rituals, auspicious timings, festivals, and celestial positions, serving as a spiritual and practical guide in daily life.

yogResponse.yogMeaning: Individuals born under this yoga have a cheerful disposition. They are introspective (introverted) while being discerning. Their social status is better.
yogResponse.remedies: हर्षण योग में आनंद और प्रसन्नता से जुड़े कार्यों को शुभ माना जाता है, जैसे उत्सव, मिलन, संगीत, कला, खेल और नई परियोजनाएँ। हालांकि, शोक, अशांति, निराशा और विवादास्पद गतिविधियों से इस योग में बचना चाहिए।

panchangKaranResponse.karanSummary: विष्टि को भद्रा के नाम से जाना जाता है। इसे किसी भी महत्वपूर्ण कार्य के लिए अशुभ करण माना जाता है। इस कारण में शुरू किए गए काम में सफलता की संभावनाएं कम हो सकती हैं।
